title: Workers To Spend 3 Days Repairing I-90 Bridge Over I-29
text:
Workers To Spend 3 Days Repairing I-90 Bridge Over I-29 October 15, 2015, 6:18 AM SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
South Dakota Department of Transportation workers will be repairing the bridge deck in the westbound lanes of the Interstate 90 bridge over Interstate 29 for the next three days. The DOT will be reducing westbound I-90 to one lane through the interchange during construction, and the speed limit is being lowered to 45 mph. Officials say ramp traffic will be maintained throughout the project but the space for merging traffic will be limited. Drivers are asked to slow down and be aware of suddenly slowing and merging traffic both through the interchange and on the ramps. Â© 2015 Associated Press. All rights reserved.
